  "title": "Student Care Teacher",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Implement the program for the class in accordance with the policies, guidelines, framework and philosophy of the centre.</li><li>Guide primary school children (primary 1 to 6) to ensure completion of daily homework</li><li>Keep accurate records of children’s progress and address each child’s educational and developmental needs on an individual basis to the best of your ability.</li><li>Responsible for the preparation and upkeep of teaching resources, arrangement, appearance and learning environment of the classroom.</li><li>Maintain and build relationships with children and parents.</li><li>Conduct enrichment programmes.</li><li>Ensure safety and timely transfer of students from school to student centre</li><li>Ensure safety of children within the premises</li><li>Any other ad-hoc duties as delegated by Centre Director</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Able to teach primary school subjects: English, Math, Science, Mandarin</strong></li><li>Possess good communication and classroom management skills</li><li>Enthusiastic & energetic and has a positive mindset to learn and grow together with the company.</li><li>Creative and loving energy with a positive disposition</li><li>Excellent communication and classroom management skills</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><ul><li>On-job-training provided</li><li>Full-time / part-time positions</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Candidate who is keen in building a solid teaching career and be a part of the <em>‘kampung spirit’</em> team is warmly welcome to send an updated resume to <strong>hr.dncedu@gmail.com</strong></p><p><br /></p>",
